==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dynamometer
<hw>Dy`na*mom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>dynamom⟦egrave⟧tre</ets>. See <er>Dynameter</er>.]</ety> <def>An
apparatus for measuring force or power; especially, muscular effort of
men or animals, or the power developed by a motor, or that required to
operate machinery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ It usually embodies a spring to be compressed or weight
to be sustained by the force applied, combined with an index, or
automatic recorder, to show the work performed.</note></p>

<p><ent>Dynamometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Dynamometric</ent>⟦br⟧
